    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen using the global statusline (`laststatus=3`), the connector characters (`├`, `┬`, etc) are sometimes overwritten by plain separators (`│`, `─`) when navigating between windows.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nFirst, create a `repro.lua` w/ the following settings and run `nvim -u repro.lua`:\n\n```lua\nvim.opt.laststatus = 3\nvim.api.nvim_set_hl(0, \"NormalNC\", { bg = \"#282828\" })\n```\n\nThe bug can be reproduced in both the vertical and horizontal axes. For the vertical axis, run `:vsplit | wincmd l | split` to create the following layout:\n\n```\n┌──────┬──────┐\n│      │ topR │\n│ left ├──────┤\n│      │ botR │\n└──────┴──────┘\n```\n\nThen move the focus from the bottom right split to the left one. The `├` joiner will be replaced by a `│` after the switch.\n\nFor the horizontal axis, create this layout:\n\n```\n┌─────────────┐\n│     top     │\n├──────┬──────┤\n│ botL │ botR │\n└──────┴──────┘\n```\n\nAnd move the focus from the bottom right split to the top one. Again, the `┬` joiner is replaced by `─`.\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/4d20b89a-0ae7-4a36-93f1-509c98f67679\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe joiner characters don't change after switching focus.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-nightly+57fc77e\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 15.7\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.2.3\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nNix flake",
